{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UoLnDrqxbRCpjjzeDMurDe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals are met. Here's the summary of what was wrong and what was fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** `app-user` had write and read permissions on the `/app` vhost, but the **configure** permission was empty (`\"\"`). RabbitMQ requires configure permission matching the queue name to declare (create) a queue. Without it, the AMQP `queue.declare` call returned `Access refused`.\n\n**Fix:** Granted full permissions to `app-user` on `/app`:\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"\n```\n\n**Verified state:**\n- `app-producer` is `1/1 Running` (0 restarts since fix)\n- `/app` vhost contains `app-queue` of type **classic** with **50 messages**\n- All 3 RabbitMQ nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) are running, no alarms, no network partitions"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2043,"cache_read_input_tokens":32398,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2043},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04fced7f-f30a-46a1-9834-8d5995256a68","uuid":"8aabf84e-57eb-4b30-918d-7b16c70f277f","request_id":"req_011Ccc1SG3RGGFXdHeZgbuXz"}
